The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's stance on immigration and refugees. It emphasizes the importance of a responsible approach to refugees, which involves eventually returning them to their home countries to help rebuild. The article also highlights America's leading role in global refugee efforts, both in terms of financial contributions and permanent resettlement. President Trump has signed an Executive Order to enhance State and local involvement in refugee resettlement. The President's priority is to put the welfare of American citizens first and ensure the safety and security of the American people by vetting those admitted into the country.